  <body><![CDATA[Yeah, I've found that John Green just can't seem the shuck the chains of the Manic Pixie Dream Girl. This time it's just a guy instead of a girl. I did like how sometimes Hazel called him out on it, at least in her mind. Like when they were at the art park, and later she was like "that seemed so fake" and I was like "THANK YOU." But, you know, I forgave him because he stomped on my heart at the end. <br />Also one thing that was a minor annoyance: the "ghettoization of eggs as breakfast food?" What a hipster nonimportant thing to worry about. But maybe that was the point? But it didn't feel like the point, it felt like Hazel (and Green) though it was genuinely important? Idk! <br />But otherwise, brilliant novel. DFTBA!]]></body>
  
