  <body><![CDATA[I don't know you, so I hope you will excuse my intrusion on your review. I've been a fan of Green's for years, but this book stopped me dead in my tracks. <br /><br />Kudos to you for recognizing what it is truly about, as I am a childhood leukemia survivor, and it about knocked me over cold with its Truths (with a capital T, because that is what they are). <br /><br />I've waited a long time for someone to capture the life of a teenaged cancer patient without all the ridiculous melodrama and profound moments tuned to whiny string orchestras. Green captured it in all its essence, and for that I am humbled....]]></body>
  
