        <comment>
  <id>88408980</id>
  <body><![CDATA[I was just about to comment and point that out: cigarette companies make money from people buying their product, and they don't really care what anyone does afterwards. Obviously they prefer that you smoke the cigarettes and fuel your addiction, therefore buying more, but the point is that with every pack he buys, Augustus directly funds an organization that gives people cancer. <br /><br />And it's true that if you don't light the cigarette you "can't give them the power to give you cancer" but that's not the point. You bought the cigarettes, therefore you gave money to the cigarette companies, and they will spend that money making more cigarettes that will then <i>give people cancer</i>.]]></body>
  
