  <body><![CDATA[Madeline : <br /><br />This is such an awesome review! When you say you review every read; YOU REVIEW EVERY READ! I have been wanting to read this book for a fresh easy read for some time now . Sometimes my book club , which I REALLY LOVE don't get me wrong , includes some very challenging reads. I like mysteries dealing with a great bit of psychological and analytical thinking about the complex characters , unfamiliar settings, and ways of life that bring up very challenging conflicts. Our group reads Historical Southern Gothic or as my cousin Larry Brown called it Southern Grit Lit. <br /><br />I guess it is like the indie rock of reading or maybe some bluegrass indie in there too!! HA! The Writers and the musicians inspire each other as well as the country home cooked foods and their beverage of choice from Sweet Tea and Lemonade to straight up Wild Turkey on the Rocks or Yalabusha brewed Beer. <br /><br />Now some of the pre- 1980 reads take place during prohibition times and the post - 1980 reads can take place in the Ozarks where all money is made in Meth. labs . After I have had to much darkness, I need some easy reads too calm my soul!!! LOL ! <br /><br />Now I want this one and I have Donna's new book. If the new book connects a little to Secret History , I might need to speed read a little to remind myself of some specifics from that old favorite. I wish she would write more than one book every Blue Moon ! You definitely have the same taste I have in reading. I really don't do FooFoo reads unless there is just nothing around to read. My Aunt Jane got the idea one year I liked Nicholas Sparks just because I did like The Notebook. Now she always try's to give me his books. Sad! I do break down and read them eventually . HA! <br /><br />Loved the reviews ... I am going to try to get a new MAC this week. Cross your fingers. My brand new Windows 8 died last April when an old classmate from high school became fixated on me when he found me on FaceBook. I was cautioned about his changed behavior so he sent lovely gifts ( viruses, key loggers, stealth genie spies and even got into my icloud) that ended my tech days until just recently! I got an iPad Air in November. Love it! But it is not a whole computer. I will never use windows again until they put money into a security system. Apple is finally save after their latest upgrade to IOS7. <br />Be careful out there Miss Madeline . There are bad men everywhere! Good night moon! Your Little Friend, Dawn]]></body>
  
