        <comment>
  <id>92109802</id>
  <body><![CDATA[Okay, but here's the thing: Hazel Grace is not Esther Earl. John Green has said over and over that Hazel is nothing like Esther. The foundations for this book were laid fifteen years ago, when Green was working at a children's hospital and observing kids going through life-threatening illnesses. It's likely that Green's friendship with Esther was what finally gave him the method of approaching this story (which, again, he has been trying to write since he was in his early twenties), but <i>The Fault in Our Stars</i> is not about Esther Earl. It may seem callous of me to say this, but <i>The Fault in Our Stars</i> was always about John Green. Every John Green book is about John Green, first and foremost.]]></body>
  
